"script": "If you could find a bathtub big enough, Saturn would float in it. This giant is the second largest planet in our solar system, yet it's made mostly of light gases like hydrogen. That makes it less dense than water, the only planet in the Sun's family that could bob on the surface instead of sinking. But don't picture a gentle soak. Underneath those calm-looking rings, winds scream around the planet at over 1,000 miles per hour. So Saturn would float in your tub, while a storm bigger than Earth raged across its clouds.",
